{{ESC National Year | Year = 1985 | Country = Greece | Preselection = Internal Selection | Preselection date = | Entrant = [[Takis Biniaris]] | Song = [[Miazoume]] | Writer = [[Takis Biniaris]] | Final result = 16th, 15 points | Prev = 1984 | Next = 1987 }} '''Greece''' was represented by [[Takis Biniaris]] with the song "[[Miazoume]]", at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1985|1985 Eurovision Song Contest]], which took place on 4 May in [[Gothenburg]], [[Sweden]]. The song was chosen internally by broadcaster [[Hellenic Broadcasting Corporation|ERT]]. [[Greece in the Eurovision Song Contest|Greece]] withdrew, having been drawn eighteenth in order of presentation. The reason behind the withdrawal, was that the Eurovision contest coincided with Holy Saturday. Their entry would have been "Wagon-lit" (βάγκον λι) performed by [[Polina Misailidou|Polina]].
== At Eurovision == Takis Biniaris was the nineteenth and last performer on the night of the contest, following [[Luxembourg]]. At the close of voting, "Miazoume" had received 15 points, placing Greece 16th of the 19. The Greek jury awarded its 12 points to [[France]].<ref>[http://www.esc-history.com/details.asp?key=545 ESC History - Greece 1985]</ref>
