'''Roadmage''' is a [[street magic|street magic act]] created by [[Illusionist|magician]] and [[entertainer]] Owen Lean.

Since 2002, Roadmage has been a fixture on [[Dublin]]'s [[Grafton Street]], [[London]]'s [[Covent Garden]], [[Granville Island]] in [[Vancouver]] and at club<ref name=londonpaper>[http://www.roadmage.com/Londonpaper.jpg] Scan of The London Paper 30 April 2009, article on the Open Wand club night at which the act regularly featured</ref>{{Citation broken|date=January 2018}} and festival<ref name=Magicweek>[http://www.magicweek.co.uk/backissues_0200-0249/0227.htm] Back issue of Magicweek mentioning the act being chosen to represent Ireland at the Singapore River Buskers Festival</ref> venues. When Lean graduated in November 2006, the act, with Lean performing in full academical attire on Grafton Street, made national news,<ref name=IrishExaminer>[http://www.roadmage.com/irisharticles/irishexaminer.jpg] Scan of Irish Examiner 10 November 2006</ref>{{Citation broken|date=January 2018}}<ref name=IrishStar>[http://www.roadmage.com/irisharticles/irishStar.jpg] Scan of Irish Star 10 November 2006</ref>{{Citation broken|date=January 2018}}<ref name=IrishIndy>[http://www.roadmage.com/irisharticles/irishindy.jpg] Scan of Irish Independent 10 November 2006</ref>{{Citation broken|date=January 2018}} including the front page of [[The Irish Times]].<ref name=IrishTimes>[http://www.roadmage.com/irisharticles/timesfront.jpg Irish Times Cover] Scan of Irish Times front cover 10 November 2006</ref>{{Citation broken|date=January 2018}}

